{{refimprove|date=May 2012}} {{Infobox School | name = KAIS International School | native_name = | image = | imagesize = | caption = School logo | location = [[Shinagawa, Tokyo]], Japan | streetaddress = 2-7-16 Kami-Osaki | coordinates = {{coord|35|38|16.5|N|139|42|59.3|E|region:JP-13_type:edu}} | established = | founder = | principal = Thomas House | headmaster = | schooltype = Private international | enrollment = | motto = Knowledge, Academia, Inspiration, Spirit | colors = Black & blue | telephone = | faxnumber = | website = http://www.kaischool.com }}
'''KAIS International School''' (formerly Kikokushijo Academy International School) is an international school located in [[Shinagawa, Tokyo]], Japan. KAIS provides an English-based education to international junior high and high school students living in Tokyo.
KAIS International School offers programs for grades 7-12 and integrates [[SAT]] preparation, art, photography, theater, and other creative classes, yoga, science laboratories, team sports, digital music composition, academic writing, and literature classes into its California-benchmark based curriculum. KAIS's educational philosophy is based on small class sizes, and is influenced by [[Rudolf Steiner|Steiner]] and [[Montessori]] educational theory. It uses the "One MacBook per student" educational philosophy, and is affiliated with [[Kikokushijo Academy]] in Setagaya.
