'''Kyle R. Cave''' is a professor of [[psychology]] at [[UMass Amherst]].  His primary research interest is visual [[Selective attention]], and he also teaches courses in [[Cognitive Psychology]] and [[Consciousness]].

His most important contribution is the [[FeatureGate]] model of attentional selection.

