[[File:Iraq-National unity ballet2 600.jpg|thumb|right|Two ballet dancers of the [[Iraqi National Ballet]] (which is based in Baghdad) performing a ballet show in [[Iraq]] in 2007.]]

'''The Music and Ballet School of Baghdad''' ([[Arabic]],مدرسة بغداد للموسيقى و الباليه) was founded in [[Baghdad]], [[Iraq]] in 1967. It was initially opened as part of [[Saddam Hussein]]'s secularist cultural campaign.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB120528749444329381 | title=Baghdad Music and Ballet School Soldiers On | work=[[Wall Street Journal]] | date=March 12, 2008 | accessdate=October 19, 2011 | author=Kaylan, Melik}}</ref>

Teachers from the [[Bolshoi Theater]] in Russia came to Baghdad to teach.{{fact|date=October 2011}} At present{{when|date=October 2011}} the teaching staff are fully Iraqi.{{fact|date=October 2011}}

In March 2016, the Associated Press reported that the school was facing financial difficulties owing to the government's budgetary crisis.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.sfchronicle.com/news/world/article/Iraq-s-only-ballet-and-music-school-faces-funding-6895156.php|title = Iraq's only ballet and music school faces funding crisis|website = San Francisco Chronicle|access-date = 2016-03-17}}</ref> According to the report, the [[Ministry of Culture (Iraq)|Ministry of Culture]] had ordered the school to begin charging tuition.

